5632
5633void Spell::EffectStealBeneficialBuff(SpellEffIndex effIndex)
5634{
5635 if (effectHandleMode != SPELL_EFFECT_HANDLE_HIT_TARGET)
5636 return;
5637
5638 LOG_DEBUG("spells.aura", "Effect: StealBeneficialBuff");
5639
5640 if (!unitTarget || unitTarget == m_caster) // can't steal from self
5641 return;
5642
5643 DispelChargesList steal_list;
5644
5645 // Create dispel mask by dispel type
5646 uint32 dispelMask = SpellInfo::GetDispelMask(DispelType(m_spellInfo->Effects[effIndex].MiscValue));
5647 Unit::AuraMap const& auras = unitTarget->GetOwnedAuras();
5648 for (Unit::AuraMap::const_iterator itr = auras.begin(); itr != auras.end(); ++itr)
5649 {
5650 Aura* aura = itr->second;
5651 AuraApplication* aurApp = aura->GetApplicationOfTarget(unitTarget->GetGUID());
5652 if (!aurApp)
5653 continue;
5654
5655 if ((aura->GetSpellInfo()->GetDispelMask()) & dispelMask)
5656 {
5657 // Need check for passive? this
5658 if (!aurApp->IsPositive() || aura->IsPassive() || aura->GetSpellInfo()->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR4_CANNOT_BE_STOLEN))
5659 continue;
5660
5661 // The charges / stack amounts don't count towards the total number of auras that can be dispelled.
5662 // Ie: A dispel on a target with 5 stacks of Winters Chill and a Polymorph has 1 / (1 + 1) -> 50% chance to dispell
5663 // Polymorph instead of 1 / (5 + 1) -> 16%.
5664 bool dispel_charges = aura->GetSpellInfo()->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR7_DISPEL_REMOVES_CHARGES);
5665 uint8 charges = dispel_charges ? aura->GetCharges() : aura->GetStackAmount();
5666 if (charges > 0)
5667 steal_list.push_back(std::make_pair(aura, charges));
5668 }
5669 }
5670
5671 if (steal_list.empty())
5672 return;
5673
5674 // Ok if exist some buffs for dispel try dispel it
5675 uint32 failCount = 0;
5676 DispelList success_list;
5677 WorldPacket dataFail(SMSG_DISPEL_FAILED, 8 + 8 + 4 + 4 + damage * 4);
5678 // dispel N = damage buffs (or while exist buffs for dispel)
5679 for (int32 count = 0; count < damage && !steal_list.empty();)
5680 {
5681 // Random select buff for dispel
5682 DispelChargesList::iterator itr = steal_list.begin();
5683 std::advance(itr, urand(0, steal_list.size() - 1));
5684
5685 int32 chance = itr->first->CalcDispelChance(unitTarget, !unitTarget->IsFriendlyTo(m_caster));
5686 // 2.4.3 Patch Notes: "Dispel effects will no longer attempt to remove effects that have 100% dispel resistance."
5687 if (!chance)
5688 {
5689 steal_list.erase(itr);
5690 continue;
5691 }
5692 else
5693 {
5694 if (roll_chance_i(chance))
5695 {
5696 success_list.push_back(std::make_pair(itr->first->GetId(), itr->first->GetCasterGUID()));
5697 --itr->second;
5698 if (itr->second <= 0)
5699 steal_list.erase(itr);
5700 }
5701 else
5702 {
5703 if (!failCount)
5704 {
5705 // Failed to dispell
5706 dataFail << m_caster->GetGUID(); // Caster GUID
5707 dataFail << unitTarget->GetGUID(); // Victim GUID
5708 dataFail << uint32(m_spellInfo->Id); // dispel spell id
5709 }
5710 ++failCount;
5711 dataFail << uint32(itr->first->GetId()); // Spell Id
5712 }
5713 ++count;
5714 }
5715 }
5716
5717 if (failCount)
5718 m_caster->SendMessageToSet(&dataFail, true);
5719
5720 if (success_list.empty())
5721 return;
5722
5723 WorldPacket dataSuccess(SMSG_SPELLSTEALLOG, 8 + 8 + 4 + 1 + 4 + damage * 5);
5724 dataSuccess << unitTarget->GetPackGUID(); // Victim GUID
5725 dataSuccess << m_caster->GetPackGUID(); // Caster GUID
5726 dataSuccess << uint32(m_spellInfo->Id); // dispel spell id
5727 dataSuccess << uint8(0); // not used
5728 dataSuccess << uint32(success_list.size()); // count
5729 for (DispelList::iterator itr = success_list.begin(); itr != success_list.end(); ++itr)
5730 {
5731 dataSuccess << uint32(itr->first); // Spell Id
5732 dataSuccess << uint8(0); // 0 - steals !=0 transfers
5733 unitTarget->RemoveAurasDueToSpellBySteal(itr->first, itr->second, m_caster);
5734 }
5735 m_caster->SendMessageToSet(&dataSuccess, true);
5736}

5821void Spell::EffectActivateRune(SpellEffIndex effIndex)
5822{
5823 if (effectHandleMode != SPELL_EFFECT_HANDLE_LAUNCH)
5824 return;
5825
5826 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
5827 return;
5828
5829 Player* player = m_caster->ToPlayer();
5830
5831 if (player->getClass() != CLASS_DEATH_KNIGHT)
5832 return;
5833
5834 // needed later
5835 m_runesState = m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetRunesState();
5836
5837 uint32 count = damage;
5838 if (count == 0) count = 1;
5839 for (uint32 j = 0; j < MAX_RUNES && count > 0; ++j)
5840 {
5841 if (player->GetRuneCooldown(j) && player->GetCurrentRune(j) == RuneType(m_spellInfo->Effects[effIndex].MiscValue))
5842 {
5843 if (m_spellInfo->Id == 45529)
5844 if (player->GetBaseRune(j) != RuneType(m_spellInfo->Effects[effIndex].MiscValueB))
5845 continue;
5846 player->SetRuneCooldown(j, 0);
5847 player->SetGracePeriod(j, player->IsInCombat()); // xinef: reset grace period
5848 --count;
5849 }
5850 }
5851
5852 // Blood Tap
5853 if (m_spellInfo->Id == 45529 && count > 0)
5854 {
5855 for (uint32 l = 0; l < MAX_RUNES && count > 0; ++l)
5856 {
5857 // Check if both runes are on cd as that is the only time when this needs to come into effect
5858 if ((player->GetRuneCooldown(l) && player->GetCurrentRune(l) == RuneType(m_spellInfo->Effects[effIndex].MiscValueB)) && (player->GetRuneCooldown(l + 1) && player->GetCurrentRune(l + 1) == RuneType(m_spellInfo->Effects[effIndex].MiscValueB)))
5859 {
5860 // Should always update the rune with the lowest cd
5861 if (player->GetRuneCooldown(l) >= player->GetRuneCooldown(l + 1))
5862 l++;
5863 player->SetRuneCooldown(l, 0);
5864 player->SetGracePeriod(l, player->IsInCombat()); // xinef: reset grace period
5865 --count;
5866 }
5867 else
5868 break;
5869 }
5870 }
5871
5872 // Empower rune weapon
5873 if (m_spellInfo->Id == 47568)
5874 {
5875 // Need to do this just once
5876 if (effIndex != 0)
5877 return;
5878
5879 for (uint32 i = 0; i < MAX_RUNES; ++i)
5880 {
5881 if (player->GetRuneCooldown(i) && (player->GetCurrentRune(i) == RUNE_FROST || player->GetCurrentRune(i) == RUNE_DEATH))
5882 {
5883 player->SetRuneCooldown(i, 0);
5884 player->SetGracePeriod(i, player->IsInCombat()); // xinef: reset grace period
5885 }
5886 }
5887 }
5888
5889 // is needed to push through to the client that the rune is active
5890 //player->ResyncRunes(MAX_RUNES);
5891 m_caster->CastSpell(m_caster, 47804, true);
5892}

5894void Spell::EffectCreateTamedPet(SpellEffIndex effIndex)
5895{
5896 if (effectHandleMode != SPELL_EFFECT_HANDLE_HIT_TARGET)

5912

5914

5916 {
5917 pet->SavePetToDB(PET_SAVE_AS_CURRENT);
5918 unitTarget->ToPlayer()->PetSpellInitialize();
5919 }

6007
6008void Spell::SummonGuardian(uint32 i, uint32 entry, SummonPropertiesEntry const* properties, uint32 numGuardians)
6009{
6010 Unit* caster = m_originalCaster;
6011 if (!caster)
6012 return;
6013
6014 if (caster->IsTotem())
6015 caster = caster->ToTotem()->GetOwner();
6016
6017 // in another case summon new
6018 uint8 summonLevel = caster->getLevel();
6019
6020 // level of pet summoned using engineering item based at engineering skill level
6021 if (m_CastItem && caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
6022 if (ItemTemplate const* proto = m_CastItem->GetTemplate())
6023 {
6024 // xinef: few special cases
6025 if (proto->RequiredSkill == SKILL_ENGINEERING)
6026 {
6027 if (uint16 skill202 = caster->ToPlayer()->GetSkillValue(SKILL_ENGINEERING))
6028 summonLevel = skill202 / 5;
6029 }
6030
6031 switch (m_spellInfo->Id)
6032 {
6033 // Dragon's Call
6034 case 13049:
6035 summonLevel = 55;
6036 break;
6037
6038 // Cleansed Timberling Heart: Summon Timberling
6039 case 5666:
6040 summonLevel = 7;
6041 break;
6042
6043 // Glowing Cat Figurine: Summon Ghost Saber
6044 case 6084:
6045 // minLevel 19, maxLevel 20
6046 summonLevel = 20;
6047 break;
6048
6049 // Spiked Collar: Summon Felhunter
6050 case 8176:
6051 summonLevel = 30;
6052 break;
6053
6054 // Dog Whistle: Summon Tracking Hound
6055 case 9515:
6056 summonLevel = 30;
6057 break;
6058
6059 // Barov Peasant Caller: Death by Peasant
6060 case 18307:
6061 case 18308:
6062 summonLevel = 60;
6063 break;
6064
6065 // Thornling Seed: Plant Thornling
6066 case 22792:
6067 summonLevel = 60;
6068 break;
6069
6070 // Cannonball Runner: Summon Crimson Cannon
6071 case 6251:
6072 summonLevel = 61;
6073 break;
6074 }
6075 }
6076
6077 summonLevel = std::min<uint8>(sWorld->getIntConfig(CONFIG_MAX_PLAYER_LEVEL) + sWorld->getIntConfig(CONFIG_WORLD_BOSS_LEVEL_DIFF), std::max<uint8>(1U, summonLevel));
6078
6079 float radius = 5.0f;
6080 int32 duration = m_spellInfo->GetDuration();
6081
6082 if (Player* modOwner = m_originalCaster->GetSpellModOwner())
6083 modOwner->ApplySpellMod(m_spellInfo->Id, SPELLMOD_DURATION, duration);
6084
6085 //TempSummonType summonType = (duration == 0) ? TEMPSUMMON_DEAD_DESPAWN : TEMPSUMMON_TIMED_DESPAWN;
6086 Map* map = caster->GetMap();
6087 TempSummon* summon = nullptr;
6088
6089 uint32 currMinionsCount = m_caster->m_Controlled.size();
6090 uint32 totalNumGuardians = numGuardians + currMinionsCount;
6091
6092 for (uint32 count = 0; count < numGuardians; ++count)
6093 {
6094 Position pos;
6095
6096 // xinef: do not use precalculated position for effect summon pet in this function
6097 // it means it was cast by NPC and should have its position overridden
6098 if (totalNumGuardians == 1 && GetSpellInfo()->Effects[i].Effect != SPELL_EFFECT_SUMMON_PET)
6099 {
6100 pos = *destTarget;
6101 }
6102 else
6103 {
6104 // randomize position
6105 pos = m_caster->GetRandomPoint(*destTarget, radius);
6106 }
6107
6108 summon = map->SummonCreature(entry, pos, properties, duration, caster, m_spellInfo->Id);
6109 if (!summon)
6110 return;
6111
6112 // xinef: set calculated level
6113 summon->SetLevel(summonLevel);
6114
6115 // if summonLevel changed, set stats for calculated level
6116 if (summonLevel != caster->getLevel())
6117 {
6118 ((Guardian*)summon)->InitStatsForLevel(summonLevel);
6119 }
6120
6121 // xinef: if we have more than one guardian, change follow angle
6122 if (summon->HasUnitTypeMask(UNIT_MASK_MINION) && totalNumGuardians > 1)
6123 ((Minion*)summon)->SetFollowAngle(m_caster->GetAbsoluteAngle(pos.GetPositionX(), pos.GetPositionY()));
6124 //else if (summon->HasUnitTypeMask(UNIT_MASK_MINION) && m_targets.HasDst())
6125 // ((Minion*)summon)->SetFollowAngle(m_caster->GetAngle(summon));
6126
6127 // xinef: move this here, some auras are added in initstatsforlevel!
6128 if (!summon->IsInCombat() && !summon->IsTrigger())
6129 {
6130 // summon->AI()->EnterEvadeMode();
6131 summon->GetMotionMaster()->Clear(false);
6132 summon->GetMotionMaster()->MoveFollow(caster, PET_FOLLOW_DIST, summon->GetFollowAngle(), MOTION_SLOT_ACTIVE);
6133 }
6134
6135 if (properties && properties->Category == SUMMON_CATEGORY_ALLY)
6136 summon->SetFaction(caster->GetFaction());
6137
6138 ExecuteLogEffectSummonObject(i, summon);
6139 }
6140
6141 // Summon infernal, cast enslave demon
6142 // xinef: have to do it here because in Pet init stats infernal is not in world, imo this should be changed...
6143 if (summon)
6144 {
6145 switch (m_spellInfo->Id)
6146 {
6147 // Inferno, Warlock summon spell
6148 case 1122:
6149 caster->AddAura(61191, summon);
6150 break;
6151 // Ritual of Doom, Warlock summon spell
6152 case 60478:
6153 caster->AddAura(SPELL_RITUAL_ENSLAVEMENT, summon);
6154 break;
6155 }
6156 }
6157}

6276void Spell::EffectCastButtons(SpellEffIndex effIndex)
6277{
6278 if (effectHandleMode != SPELL_EFFECT_HANDLE_HIT)
6279 return;
6280
6281 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
6282 return;
6283
6284 Player* p_caster = m_caster->ToPlayer();
6285 uint32 button_id = m_spellInfo->Effects[effIndex].MiscValue + 132;
6286 uint32 n_buttons = m_spellInfo->Effects[effIndex].MiscValueB;
6287
6288 for (; n_buttons; --n_buttons, ++button_id)
6289 {
6290 ActionButton const* ab = p_caster->GetActionButton(button_id);
6291 if (!ab || ab->GetType() != ACTION_BUTTON_SPELL)
6292 continue;
6293
6296 uint32 spell_id = ab->GetAction();
6297 if (!spell_id)
6298 continue;
6299
6300 SpellInfo const* spellInfo = sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(spell_id);
6301 if (!spellInfo)
6302 continue;
6303
6304 if (!p_caster->HasSpell(spell_id) || p_caster->HasSpellCooldown(spell_id))
6305 continue;
6306
6307 if (!spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR7_CAN_BE_MULTI_CAST))
6308 continue;
6309
6310 uint32 cost = spellInfo->CalcPowerCost(m_caster, spellInfo->GetSchoolMask(), this);
6311 if (m_caster->GetPower(POWER_MANA) < cost)
6312 continue;
6313
6314 TriggerCastFlags triggerFlags = TriggerCastFlags(TRIGGERED_IGNORE_GCD | TRIGGERED_IGNORE_CAST_IN_PROGRESS | TRIGGERED_CAST_DIRECTLY);
6315 m_caster->CastSpell(m_caster, spell_id, triggerFlags);
6316 }
6317}

6319void Spell::EffectRechargeManaGem(SpellEffIndex /*effIndex*/)
6320{
6321 if (effectHandleMode != SPELL_EFFECT_HANDLE_HIT_TARGET)
6322 return;
6323
6324 if (!unitTarget || unitTarget->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
6325 return;
6326
6327 Player* player = m_caster->ToPlayer();
6328
6329 if (!player)
6330 return;
6331
6332 uint32 item_id = m_spellInfo->Effects[EFFECT_0].ItemType;
6333
6334 ItemTemplate const* pProto = sObjectMgr->GetItemTemplate(item_id);
6335 if (!pProto)
6336 {
6337 player->SendEquipError(EQUIP_ERR_ITEM_NOT_FOUND, nullptr, nullptr);
6338 return;
6339 }
6340
6341 if (Item* pItem = player->GetItemByEntry(item_id))
6342 {
6343 for (int x = 0; x < MAX_ITEM_PROTO_SPELLS; ++x)
6344 pItem->SetSpellCharges(x, pProto->Spells[x].SpellCharges);
6345 pItem->SetState(ITEM_CHANGED, player);
6346 }
6347}

6349void Spell::EffectBind(SpellEffIndex effIndex)
6350{
6351 if (effectHandleMode != SPELL_EFFECT_HANDLE_HIT_TARGET)
6352 return;
6353
6354 if (!unitTarget)
6355 return;
6356
6357 Player* player = unitTarget->ToPlayer();
6358 if (!player)
6359 {
6360 return;
6361 }
6362
6363 WorldLocation homeLoc;
6364 uint32 areaId = player->GetAreaId();
6365
6366 if (m_spellInfo->Effects[effIndex].MiscValue)
6367 areaId = m_spellInfo->Effects[effIndex].MiscValue;
6368
6369 if (m_targets.HasDst())
6370 homeLoc.WorldRelocate(*destTarget);
6371 else
6372 {
6373 homeLoc = player->GetWorldLocation();
6374 }
6375
6376 player->SetHomebind(homeLoc, areaId);
6377
6378 // binding
6379 WorldPacket data(SMSG_BINDPOINTUPDATE, 4 + 4 + 4 + 4 + 4);
6380 data << float(homeLoc.GetPositionX());
6381 data << float(homeLoc.GetPositionY());
6382 data << float(homeLoc.GetPositionZ());
6383 data << uint32(homeLoc.GetMapId());
6384 data << uint32(areaId);
6385 player->SendDirectMessage(&data);
6386
6387 LOG_DEBUG("spells.aura", "EffectBind: New homebind X: {}, Y: {}, Z: {}, MapId: {}, AreaId: {}",
6388 homeLoc.GetPositionX(), homeLoc.GetPositionY(), homeLoc.GetPositionZ(), homeLoc.GetMapId(), areaId);
6389 // zone update
6390 data.Initialize(SMSG_PLAYERBOUND, 8 + 4);
6391 data << m_caster->GetGUID();
6392 data << uint32(areaId);
6393 player->SendDirectMessage(&data);
6394}

6399 return;
6400
6401 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)

6419 data << uint32(MAX_PLAYER_SUMMON_DELAY * IN_MILLISECONDS); // auto decline after msecs
